+{"id":"franken_numpy-dz6k","title":"Preserve non-finite matrix norm parity","description":"## Problem\n`fnp_linalg::matrix_norm_nxn` and `matrix_norm_2x2` currently reject any non-finite matrix entries. The public 2-D `UFuncArray::norm()` bridge routes into `matrix_norm_nxn`, so calls analogous to `np.linalg.norm([[nan, 1.0], [2.0, 3.0]])` fail instead of following NumPy behavior.\n\n## Evidence\n- `matrix_norm_nxn` currently returns `NormDetRankPolicyViolation` if any entry is non-finite\n- NumPy returns `nan` for Frobenius/1/inf-style norms on NaN matrices\n- NumPy returns `inf`, finite values, or `nan` for non-spectral norms with `inf` entries depending on the norm order\n\n## Goal\nMatch NumPy’s non-finite semantics for matrix norm orders exposed through the public API, while preserving explicit error behavior where SVD-backed spectral/nuclear norms genuinely fail on NaN input.\n\n## Files\n- `crates/fnp-linalg/src/lib.rs`\n","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","created_at":"2026-03-31T18:20:44.779438377Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-31T18:25:53.573238979Z","closed_at":"2026-03-31T18:25:53.572982544Z","close_reason":"Completed","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
